%N A098291 Chebyshev polynomials S(n,731) + S(n-1,731) with Diophantine property.
%C A098291 (27*a(n))^2 - 733*b(n)^2 = -4 with b(n)=A098292(n) give all positive solutions of this Pell equation.
%H A098291 Tanya Khovanova, <a href="http://www.tanyakhovanova.com/RecursiveSequences/RecursiveSequences.html">Recursive Sequences</a>
%H A098291 Giovanni Lucca, <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20191213181710/http://forumgeom.fau.edu/FG2019volume19/FG201902index.html">Integer Sequences and Circle Chains Inside a Hyperbola</a>, Forum Geometricorum (2019) Vol. 19, 11-16.
%H A098291 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (731,-1).
%H A098291 <a href="/index/Ch#Cheby">Index entries for sequences related to Chebyshev polynomials.</a>
%F A098291 a(n) = S(n, 731) + S(n-1, 731) = S(2*n, sqrt(733)), with S(n, x) = U(n, x/2) Chebyshev's polynomials of the second kind, A049310. S(-1, x)= 0 = U(-1, x). S(n, 731) =A098263(n).
%F A098291 a(n) = (-2/27)*i*((-1)^n)*T(2*n+1, 27*i/2) with the imaginary unit i and Chebyshev's polynomials of the first kind. See the T-triangle A053120.
%F A098291 G.f.: (1+x)/(1-731*x+x^2).
%e A098291 All positive solutions of Pell equation x^2 - 733*y^2 = -4 are (27=27*1,1), (19764=27*732,730), (14447457=27*535091,533629), (10561071303=27*391150789,390082069), ...
